 COLUMN                 |     TYPE       |    COMMENT  
 customer_id            |    string      | A unique identifier assigned to each customer, facilitating the tracking and management of customer-related information.
 customer_name          |    string      | The full name of the customer, which is essential for identification and communication purposes.
 customer_type          |    string      | Indicates the classification of the customer, such as individual or business, which aids in segmentation and targeted marketing strategies.
 credit_terms_days      |    bigint      | Represents the number of days allowed for payment after a purchase, which is important for monitoring cash flow and financial planning.
 primary_freight_type   |    string      |  Identifies the main mode of transportation used for delivery to the customer, relevant for logistics and shipping efficiency.
 account_status         |    string      |  Denotes the current status of the customer's account, helping in the assessment of account activity and overall relationship management.
 contract_start_date    |    date        |  Marks the beginning date of the customer's contract, which is crucial for tracking contract duration and related obligations.
annual_revenue_potential|   bigint       |  Estimates the total potential revenue generated from the customer over a year, useful for financial forecasting and strategic planning.


----SAMPLE DATA-----


What is the average annual revenue per customer_type?


SELECT 
    `customer_type`, 
    AVG(`annual_revenue_potential`) AS avg_annual_revenue 
FROM 
    `datawerhouse1`.`bronze`.`customers_txt`
GROUP BY 
    `customer_type`

